WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.160 --> 00:00:02.520
<i>Previously on "The Rookie"...</i>

2
00:00:02.540 --> 00:00:04.640
- What? 
- My mom died.

3
00:00:04.660 --> 00:00:06.280
Her name
is Abril Rodas.

4
00:00:06.300 --> 00:00:09.340
Her Sicarios hit
three competing gangs

5
00:00:09.350 --> 00:00:11.340
at the same time she
cut down Elijah's crew.

6
00:00:11.350 --> 00:00:13.010
Unlike La Fiera. I kill only

7
00:00:13.020 --> 00:00:14.970
when it's strategically
advantageous.

8
00:00:14.980 --> 00:00:17.760
I'll take everything away
from you until you say sorry

9
00:00:17.770 --> 00:00:19.390
for taking everything
away from me.

10
00:00:19.400 --> 00:00:21.060
Moses didn't
kill Quinlan's guys.

11
00:00:21.070 --> 00:00:24.530
Elijah did. to provoke a war.

12
00:01:10.660 --> 00:01:15.530
Relax. If I wanted to kill
you. you'd be dead already.

13
00:01:15.540 --> 00:01:19.030
This is amazing.

14
00:01:19.040 --> 00:01:20.910
I put in all this work.

15
00:01:20.920 --> 00:01:23.000
and you're just
handing me your badge.

16
00:01:25.360 --> 00:01:29.920
Tell me. Detective. is this
criminal trespass. burglary?

17
00:01:29.930 --> 00:01:32.670
Neither. I disabled
your security system.

18
00:01:32.680 --> 00:01:34.750
I was never here.

19
00:01:34.760 --> 00:01:37.170
Well. I'd better get a witness.

20
00:01:37.180 --> 00:01:40.180
Let her sleep. You
made her work hard.

21
00:01:40.190 --> 00:01:41.590
and your wife wouldn't be
happy to read about her

22
00:01:41.600 --> 00:01:43.640
in the police report.

23
00:01:43.650 --> 00:01:45.640
I also disconnected
your phone lines

24
00:01:45.650 --> 00:01:47.390
and jammed your cell.

25
00:01:50.820 --> 00:01:52.280
All right.

26
00:01:54.740 --> 00:01:57.530
If you're not here to
kill me. then what?

27
00:01:59.330 --> 00:02:01.490
I'm pregnant.

28
00:02:02.750 --> 00:02:04.160
Congratulations.

29
00:02:04.170 --> 00:02:06.870
Save it. We both know
what your end goal is.

30
00:02:06.880 --> 00:02:08.160
One day you're gonna wake up

31
00:02:08.170 --> 00:02:09.910
and decide you're
done playing with us

32
00:02:09.920 --> 00:02:11.580
and put my family in the ground.

33
00:02:11.590 --> 00:02:13.420
I would never... I'm
not wearing a wire.

34
00:02:13.430 --> 00:02:14.750
It's just us here.

35
00:02:17.270 --> 00:02:21.380
I tried to lock you up.
but I failed. You won.

36
00:02:21.390 --> 00:02:24.930
So. what. you're giving up?

37
00:02:24.940 --> 00:02:26.510
If it was just me. I'd
fight you in the street

38
00:02:26.520 --> 00:02:28.100
with a claw hammer.

39
00:02:28.110 --> 00:02:29.810
take you apart
like a horror film.

40
00:02:29.820 --> 00:02:31.600
and gladly pay the consequences.

41
00:02:31.610 --> 00:02:33.520
But I've got responsibilities
bigger than me.

42
00:02:33.530 --> 00:02:35.820
so I'm offering a trade.

43
00:02:35.830 --> 00:02:39.990
What could you possibly
have to offer me?

44
00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:44.780
Abril Rodas. She killed
eight of your men.

45
00:02:44.790 --> 00:02:47.830
We found you cowering
in a cabinet.

46
00:02:47.840 --> 00:02:54.540
I bet you still have
nightmares about her.

47
00:02:54.550 --> 00:02:57.380
Keep talking.

48
00:02:57.390 --> 00:03:01.050
She's moving north.
building her empire.

49
00:03:01.060 --> 00:03:06.350
and earning herself a
DEA/FBI/LAPD task force.

50
00:03:06.360 --> 00:03:09.270
I'm on it and offering to
feed you intel from the inside

51
00:03:09.280 --> 00:03:10.350
so you can take her out.

52
00:03:10.360 --> 00:03:11.680
Pass.

53
00:03:11.690 --> 00:03:13.900
I wasn't finished.

54
00:03:13.910 --> 00:03:15.810
You see. she knows you
were behind the hits

55
00:03:15.820 --> 00:03:17.520
on Moses' crew.

56
00:03:17.530 --> 00:03:19.280
They worked for her.

57
00:03:19.290 --> 00:03:21.440
She can't let that stand.

58
00:03:21.450 --> 00:03:25.320
So she's sending Sicarios
to put you in the ground.

59
00:03:25.330 --> 00:03:28.120
I can give you a
fighting chance.

60
00:03:28.130 --> 00:03:29.790
If she's really coming after me.

61
00:03:29.800 --> 00:03:33.080
then why not just
wait until my death?

62
00:03:33.090 --> 00:03:35.080
Because you have an
ability to come out on top

63
00:03:35.090 --> 00:03:36.630
that borders on miraculous.

64
00:03:36.640 --> 00:03:39.630
That I do.

65
00:03:39.640 --> 00:03:42.420
Which is why I'm confident I
can handle my own business.

66
00:03:42.430 --> 00:03:44.010
Don't say no just yet.

67
00:03:44.020 --> 00:03:47.180
Think hard. because my
offer has a clock on it.

68
00:03:49.070 --> 00:03:51.850
I'd rather not have
this baby in prison.

69
00:03:51.860 --> 00:03:54.940
but if you turn me down.
I won't wait for Abril.

70
00:03:54.950 --> 00:03:58.310
I'll do what I have to
do to protect my family.

71
00:03:58.320 --> 00:03:59.980
And I'll make it hurt.

72
00:04:01.410 --> 00:04:03.570
Understood.

73
00:04:27.480 --> 00:04:28.850
Let's go.

74
00:04:30.190 --> 00:04:31.810
Did he take the bait?

75
00:04:31.820 --> 00:04:34.520
He nibbled. It'll take more
to get him on the hook.

76
00:04:34.530 --> 00:04:39.270
Mm. This is a big risk.
Last chance to bow out.

77
00:04:39.280 --> 00:04:40.830
I'm all the way in.

78
00:05:00.300 --> 00:05:03.050
It's sweet.

79
00:05:03.060 --> 00:05:05.300
Yeah. No. it's a Norman
Rockwell painting...

80
00:05:05.310 --> 00:05:08.260
if Norman Rockwell was a
sociopath with a sense of humor.

81
00:05:08.270 --> 00:05:10.180
Well. I'm here with
you the whole time.

82
00:05:10.190 --> 00:05:13.100
Look. I-I'm not looking to
relive my childhood here.

83
00:05:13.110 --> 00:05:15.810
I'm just gonna get my
mom's affairs in order.

84
00:05:15.820 --> 00:05:17.850
and we'll be back in L.A. 
by tomorrow night.

85
00:05:17.860 --> 00:05:19.560
Your mom just died.

86
00:05:19.570 --> 00:05:21.650
Maybe we can change our
flight and stay a few days.

87
00:05:21.660 --> 00:05:25.400
Look. the
airline lost our luggage.

88
00:05:25.410 --> 00:05:28.490
The only rental available
was that powder-blue pillbox.

89
00:05:28.500 --> 00:05:32.290
Trust me. this is the universe
saying. "Get in and out quick."

90
00:05:36.460 --> 00:05:38.960
Oh. hey. you must be one
of Evelyn's customers.

91
00:05:38.970 --> 00:05:40.960
I'll be with you in one second.

92
00:05:40.970 --> 00:05:42.840
I'm sorry. Who are you?

93
00:05:42.850 --> 00:05:46.800
Oh. I'm her son. John Nolan.

94
00:05:46.810 --> 00:05:50.800
Really? I thought
her son was a cop.

95
00:05:50.810 --> 00:05:53.390
Protect and serve.

96
00:05:53.400 --> 00:05:55.220
You know what's weird?
That you're a cop. too?

97
00:05:55.230 --> 00:05:59.270
Yeah. And Evelyn's
only son. John Nolan.

98
00:05:59.280 --> 00:06:00.440
You want to try again?

99
00:06:00.450 --> 00:06:04.320
Josh. Cherry.

100
00:06:04.330 --> 00:06:06.110
I've heard so much about you.

101
00:06:06.120 --> 00:06:08.030
And you're impersonating me why?

102
00:06:08.040 --> 00:06:12.030
Old habit. I mean.
it was Evelyn's idea

103
00:06:12.040 --> 00:06:14.740
to help sell her line
of self-defense gear.

104
00:06:14.750 --> 00:06:16.950
She said you gave
your blessing. so...

105
00:06:16.960 --> 00:06:19.830
I haven't said a kind word
to my mother in over a year.

106
00:06:19.840 --> 00:06:21.500
Taser and pepper spray.

107
00:06:21.510 --> 00:06:24.090
"Endorsed by Captain
John Nolan. LAPD."

108
00:06:24.100 --> 00:06:25.960
You got a promotion
and didn't tell me?

109
00:06:25.970 --> 00:06:28.050
You're aware impersonating

110
00:06:28.060 --> 00:06:30.170
law enforcement is a crime?

111
00:06:30.180 --> 00:06:33.560
I can see
you need time to grieve.

112
00:06:36.940 --> 00:06:38.900
Leave the box. Josh.

113
00:06:42.070 --> 00:06:45.110
And keep my name
out of your mouth.

114
00:06:45.120 --> 00:06:48.040
Yes. sir. I'm sorry
for your loss.

115
00:06:50.080 --> 00:06:53.200
Well. that was different.

116
00:06:53.210 --> 00:06:55.990
No. that was every
day growing up.

117
00:06:56.000 --> 00:06:58.240
Well. we have a lot
of work to do here

118
00:06:58.250 --> 00:06:59.620
if we're wheels up tomorrow.

119
00:06:59.630 --> 00:07:02.210
How do you feel about
controlled burns?

120
00:07:04.220 --> 00:07:06.040
I'm not gonna be
any fun this trip.

121
00:07:06.050 --> 00:07:08.210
It's okay. 'cause
I'm enough fun for both of us.

122
00:07:08.220 --> 00:07:09.970
Mm. So true.

123
00:07:12.940 --> 00:07:15.010
I guess I should
say thank you...

124
00:07:15.020 --> 00:07:17.430
Burglary and a fourth
amendment violation.

125
00:07:17.440 --> 00:07:19.600
both under cover of authority.

126
00:07:19.610 --> 00:07:21.310
You're looking at
federal prison.

127
00:07:21.320 --> 00:07:24.020
plus a seven-figure civil
suit. And the legal fees alone

128
00:07:24.030 --> 00:07:25.810
are gonna pay for
my house in Tuscany.

129
00:07:25.820 --> 00:07:28.020
I don't know what
you're talking about.

130
00:07:28.030 --> 00:07:29.230
Give me one reason
why I shouldn't walk

131
00:07:29.240 --> 00:07:31.580
straight into Grey's office
and demand he fire you.

132
00:07:33.460 --> 00:07:36.820
Because if I get fired.
I'm useless to Elijah.

133
00:07:36.830 --> 00:07:38.830
and he's gonna need all
the help he can get.

134
00:07:38.840 --> 00:07:40.160
Has he told you about Abril?

135
00:07:40.170 --> 00:07:41.330
Blah. blah. blah.

136
00:07:41.340 --> 00:07:43.580
Yes. the world is
full of monsters.

137
00:07:43.590 --> 00:07:47.210
I'm not buying your
offer for one second.

138
00:07:47.220 --> 00:07:48.960
Who cares? You're
just an employee.

139
00:07:48.970 --> 00:07:51.960
But here's the thing...

140
00:07:51.970 --> 00:07:54.220
Abril won't see it that way.

141
00:07:54.230 --> 00:07:56.930
The people she's sending won't
care about your legal tricks.

142
00:07:56.940 --> 00:08:00.970
They will gut you just like
everyone else in Elijah's orbit.

143
00:08:00.980 --> 00:08:03.430
If you have any vacation
days. I'd take them.

144
00:08:03.440 --> 00:08:06.270
I never run from a fight.

145
00:08:06.280 --> 00:08:08.310
Fight?

146
00:08:08.320 --> 00:08:11.080
Red. you won't
even see it coming.

147
00:08:16.540 --> 00:08:18.700
You're up.

148
00:08:21.710 --> 00:08:23.580
Yeah. I'm ready.

149
00:08:23.590 --> 00:08:25.380
I'll see you at home.

150
00:08:31.260 --> 00:08:33.050
Oh. oh.

151
00:08:33.060 --> 00:08:34.520
It's okay.

152
00:08:40.230 --> 00:08:44.310
Wesley. How did
you get in here?

153
00:08:44.320 --> 00:08:49.020
Everybody has a price.
and I am very rich.

154
00:08:49.030 --> 00:08:52.320
And what exactly
have you bought?

155
00:08:52.330 --> 00:08:53.940
Besides a quick death.

156
00:08:53.950 --> 00:08:56.610
A deal with the devil. I hope.

157
00:08:56.620 --> 00:08:58.080
Moses Warden was
your man in L. A.

158
00:08:59.790 --> 00:09:01.280
And?

159
00:09:01.290 --> 00:09:02.830
I know who killed his crew...

160
00:09:02.840 --> 00:09:05.760
Well. your crew...
Disrupted your network.

161
00:09:07.130 --> 00:09:10.330
And you came all this
way just to tell me?

162
00:09:10.340 --> 00:09:12.170
How selfless of you.

163
00:09:12.180 --> 00:09:14.880
I have an agenda for sure.

164
00:09:14.890 --> 00:09:17.470
We have a mutual enemy...

165
00:09:17.480 --> 00:09:18.840
Elijah Stone.

166
00:09:18.850 --> 00:09:20.890
He stabbed La Fiera in the back.

167
00:09:20.900 --> 00:09:22.810
took over her
territory in L. A.

168
00:09:22.820 --> 00:09:25.350
Right. before you tried
to take him down yourself

169
00:09:25.360 --> 00:09:26.730
and failed.

170
00:09:26.740 --> 00:09:29.480
You and the LAPD.

171
00:09:29.490 --> 00:09:32.270
That's right. And now
he's stronger than ever.

172
00:09:32.280 --> 00:09:36.900
But the win made
him feel invincible.

173
00:09:36.910 --> 00:09:38.150
So he took out your soldiers.

174
00:09:38.160 --> 00:09:41.570
and now he's coming
for everything you own.

175
00:09:41.580 --> 00:09:47.200
And you're just willing
to hand him over to me?

176
00:09:47.210 --> 00:09:49.620
To have his death
on your conscience?

177
00:09:49.630 --> 00:09:51.210
And a lot more.

178
00:09:51.220 --> 00:09:52.710
Well. he's threatening my
family. I don't have a choice.

179
00:09:52.720 --> 00:09:55.170
Ah. How is el niño?

180
00:09:55.180 --> 00:09:57.670
He's gotten so big.

181
00:09:57.680 --> 00:10:01.050
I follow Angela online.
My secret account.

182
00:10:03.730 --> 00:10:07.520
Jack is my everything.

183
00:10:07.530 --> 00:10:08.930
And I'm gonna keep him safe.

184
00:10:08.940 --> 00:10:11.270
even if it means
making a deal with you.

185
00:10:13.570 --> 00:10:16.190
Okay.

186
00:10:16.200 --> 00:10:20.490
But you know what happens
if you betray the devil...

187
00:10:20.500 --> 00:10:24.160
To you and your niño.

188
00:10:24.170 --> 00:10:26.580
I do.

189
00:10:37.600 --> 00:10:39.420
Well. he survived first contact.

190
00:10:39.430 --> 00:10:40.970
Thank God.

191
00:10:40.980 --> 00:10:42.050
Sorry I'm late.
What did I miss?

192
00:10:42.060 --> 00:10:43.390
Abril Rodas.

193
00:10:43.400 --> 00:10:44.970
She was La Fiera's
right-hand woman

194
00:10:44.980 --> 00:10:46.810
until La Fiera went
after the wrong people

195
00:10:46.820 --> 00:10:48.520
and ended up with a
bullet in her heart.

196
00:10:48.530 --> 00:10:49.890
- Wrong people? 
- Yeah.

197
00:10:49.900 --> 00:10:51.770
She had Abril
kidnap Angela Lopez.

198
00:10:51.780 --> 00:10:53.100
She took Angela
back to Guatemala

199
00:10:53.110 --> 00:10:55.190
to steal her unborn kid.

200
00:10:55.200 --> 00:10:58.400
Small group of LAPD officers
ran an off the books...

201
00:10:58.410 --> 00:11:00.900
But sanctioned... Operation
to bring her back.

202
00:11:00.910 --> 00:11:02.700
Based on Elijah's intel.

203
00:11:02.710 --> 00:11:05.030
Angela killed La
Fiera in self-defense

204
00:11:05.040 --> 00:11:07.990
as we were escaping.
leaving Abril in charge.

205
00:11:08.000 --> 00:11:10.410
It says here Abril
doesn't sleep?

206
00:11:10.420 --> 00:11:12.040
Huh. Is that even possible?

207
00:11:12.050 --> 00:11:13.540
Well. it shouldn't be.

208
00:11:13.550 --> 00:11:15.500
Angela was with her
for a week. 24/7.

209
00:11:15.510 --> 00:11:18.460
She said she never even saw
her take as much as a cat nap.

210
00:11:18.470 --> 00:11:20.590
Fascinating. Love
to interview her.

211
00:11:20.600 --> 00:11:22.550
Yeah. well. she's got
multiple outstanding warrants.

212
00:11:22.560 --> 00:11:24.430
so she's not coming into
the States anytime soon.

213
00:11:24.440 --> 00:11:27.390
No. but her girlfriend is.
That's actually why I was late.

214
00:11:27.400 --> 00:11:30.600
Uh. DEA just intercepted a call
to Daylin Morales from Abril.

215
00:11:30.610 --> 00:11:32.350
ordering her to
come to Los Angeles.

216
00:11:32.360 --> 00:11:35.690
Rumor has it Daylin
murdered her entire family

217
00:11:35.700 --> 00:11:37.610
when she was 16
on Christmas Day.

218
00:11:37.620 --> 00:11:38.690
Abusive parents?

219
00:11:38.700 --> 00:11:40.860
No. not as far as I know.

220
00:11:40.870 --> 00:11:44.240
She taped the whole thing.
said it was her audition reel.

221
00:11:44.250 --> 00:11:45.820
And it must have worked.
'cause three months later.

222
00:11:45.830 --> 00:11:47.320
she emerges a Sicaria.

223
00:11:47.330 --> 00:11:49.660
Hooked up with Abril last year.

224
00:11:49.670 --> 00:11:53.120
Hmm. Matt. I don't have to tell
you how dangerous this plan is.

225
00:11:53.130 --> 00:11:54.620
And yet you're going to.

226
00:11:54.630 --> 00:11:56.040
You're pulling the
pin on two grenades.

227
00:11:56.050 --> 00:11:57.580
hoping to disarm them

228
00:11:57.590 --> 00:11:59.420
before they fill the
streets with blood.

229
00:11:59.430 --> 00:12:01.380
That's one way to look at it.

230
00:12:01.390 --> 00:12:02.880
And the other?

231
00:12:02.890 --> 00:12:04.350
We're playing offense. Wade.

232
00:12:06.190 --> 00:12:09.640
Are you sure you don't even
want to have a small funeral?

233
00:12:09.650 --> 00:12:11.890
Well. my mom doesn't
have any friends.

234
00:12:11.900 --> 00:12:13.310
just acquaintances.
like the grifter

235
00:12:13.320 --> 00:12:15.770
we met at the house.
and she had marks.

236
00:12:15.780 --> 00:12:18.440
Not really interested in
hearing those eulogies.

237
00:12:18.450 --> 00:12:20.520
John.

238
00:12:20.530 --> 00:12:22.070
Oh. Hey. Stacy.

239
00:12:22.080 --> 00:12:23.940
Hey. I've been
meaning to call.

240
00:12:23.950 --> 00:12:25.900
I was so sorry to
hear about your mom.

241
00:12:25.910 --> 00:12:29.030
Thank you. Stacy. this is
Bailey Nune. my fiancée.

242
00:12:29.040 --> 00:12:31.450
Hi. Fiancée?

243
00:12:31.460 --> 00:12:33.290
Good for you. I
grew up with John.

244
00:12:33.300 --> 00:12:35.080
Oh. So if I need
embarrassing stories...

245
00:12:35.090 --> 00:12:36.960
I am your girl.

246
00:12:36.970 --> 00:12:38.880
Or you could tell the time
I took on four bank robbers

247
00:12:38.890 --> 00:12:40.340
and saved your life.

248
00:12:40.350 --> 00:12:42.340
Right.
You're <i>that</i> Stacy?

249
00:12:42.350 --> 00:12:44.880
Yeah. Um. if you need
anything while you're in town.

250
00:12:44.890 --> 00:12:46.260
- please let me know. 
- Thank you.

251
00:12:46.270 --> 00:12:47.840
- Nice to meet you.
- Yeah. You. too.

252
00:12:47.850 --> 00:12:50.100
She's pretty. Did
you two ever...?

253
00:12:50.110 --> 00:12:51.510
Oh. once in high school.
but I was an idiot.

254
00:12:51.520 --> 00:12:52.520
She moved on.

255
00:12:52.520 --> 00:12:53.320
The one who got away?

256
00:12:53.320 --> 00:12:54.640
No.

257
00:12:54.650 --> 00:12:55.980
Yeah. a little.

258
00:12:55.990 --> 00:12:57.700
Oh. One second.

259
00:13:01.530 --> 00:13:04.400
Hi. Uh. Shirley. right? We
spoke on the phone this morning.

260
00:13:04.410 --> 00:13:06.320
- Uh. John Nolan. 
- Oh. yes.

261
00:13:06.330 --> 00:13:09.030
Please accept my deepest
condolences.

262
00:13:09.040 --> 00:13:11.490
Why don't I park?
Then you can come in.

263
00:13:11.500 --> 00:13:12.910
Uh. well. this will really
only just take a minute.

264
00:13:12.920 --> 00:13:14.160
John. let her park.

265
00:13:14.170 --> 00:13:15.540
It... It's fine.

266
00:13:15.550 --> 00:13:18.580
Our Platinum package
is a wonderful choice.

267
00:13:18.590 --> 00:13:20.040
Our most popular.

268
00:13:20.050 --> 00:13:21.500
Uh. that sounds
lovely. I'm thinking

269
00:13:21.510 --> 00:13:24.130
more along the lines of the
"Parental Trauma" package.

270
00:13:24.140 --> 00:13:26.010
Perhaps something
previously used.

271
00:13:26.020 --> 00:13:27.720
or just a cardboard box?

272
00:13:27.730 --> 00:13:30.010
They had a very
complicated relationship.

273
00:13:30.020 --> 00:13:33.310
I'm sorry to hear
that. Although. having known Evelyn

274
00:13:33.320 --> 00:13:35.430
for a few decades.
I'm not surprised.

275
00:13:35.440 --> 00:13:38.730
You're looking for our
most cost-effective option.

276
00:13:38.740 --> 00:13:40.100
Bingo.

277
00:13:40.110 --> 00:13:42.020
Well. then. cremation's
your best bet.

278
00:13:42.030 --> 00:13:43.610
Perfect. Uh. when
can we do that?

279
00:13:43.620 --> 00:13:44.980
This afternoon.

280
00:13:44.990 --> 00:13:47.320
Okay. Uh. just let me
know when to pick her up.

281
00:13:47.330 --> 00:13:49.240
Hey. get off the road!

282
00:13:49.250 --> 00:13:50.830
Nice to meet you.

283
00:14:11.480 --> 00:14:13.550
- What's the word? 
- Cop's intel checks out...

284
00:14:43.260 --> 00:14:46.000
Our contact in Guatemala
says Abril's mobilizing.

285
00:14:46.010 --> 00:14:47.010
Hitters are en route.

286
00:14:47.010 --> 00:14:49.210
<i>led by her girlfriend.</i>

287
00:14:49.220 --> 00:14:51.300
Hot little number.
Trying to find out more.

288
00:14:51.310 --> 00:14:53.050
We'll do it fast.

289
00:14:53.060 --> 00:14:55.890
We need to hit them before
they have time to get set up.

290
00:14:55.900 --> 00:14:58.020
Well. we could always take
up that cop on her offer.

291
00:14:58.030 --> 00:15:01.020
No. This is my city.

292
00:15:01.030 --> 00:15:03.940
Abril makes a move on me.

293
00:15:03.950 --> 00:15:05.860
we send her girlfriend
home in pieces.

294
00:15:10.500 --> 00:15:12.530
There's just so much trash.

295
00:15:12.540 --> 00:15:13.910
And we haven't
even gone upstairs.

296
00:15:13.920 --> 00:15:15.740
What are you wearing?

297
00:15:15.750 --> 00:15:18.160
Oh. I got something toxic
on my one and only shirt.

298
00:15:18.170 --> 00:15:21.000
and so I found this in a
box labeled "defective."

299
00:15:21.010 --> 00:15:23.540
"Party Aminal." What's
defective about that?

300
00:15:23.550 --> 00:15:25.080
Who the hell is this?

301
00:15:25.090 --> 00:15:28.430
I don't know. but I am
guessing it's not good.

302
00:15:34.270 --> 00:15:36.680
Is it true? The bitch is dead?

303
00:15:36.690 --> 00:15:38.140
If you're referring to
my mother. then yes.

304
00:15:38.150 --> 00:15:39.810
But I'm the only one who
gets to call her names.

305
00:15:39.820 --> 00:15:41.180
Whoa. whoa. Hold on. hold on.

306
00:15:41.190 --> 00:15:43.520
No can do. Your mom's got
something that belongs to us.

307
00:15:43.530 --> 00:15:45.350
and we want it back.

308
00:15:50.870 --> 00:15:53.360
Get out of the way now.

309
00:15:53.370 --> 00:15:55.320
Yeah.
that's a nice gun.

310
00:15:55.330 --> 00:15:57.160
I got one of those. too.

311
00:15:57.170 --> 00:15:58.460
But I also have one of these.

312
00:16:05.880 --> 00:16:09.000
Now. get in your
truck and drive away

313
00:16:09.010 --> 00:16:10.880
or I'll get my girlfriend
to beat you up. too.

314
00:16:10.890 --> 00:16:13.420
Listen. we just want to
take a quick look inside.

315
00:16:13.430 --> 00:16:15.430
You all can stay out here
and keep your nose clean.

316
00:16:15.440 --> 00:16:17.550
Unless you want me to get
local law enforcement involved.

317
00:16:17.560 --> 00:16:19.820
I suggest you get
out of here now.

318
00:16:23.530 --> 00:16:24.640
I'll see you around.

319
00:16:24.650 --> 00:16:26.030
You better hope not.

320
00:16:31.950 --> 00:16:33.610
What was that about?

321
00:16:33.620 --> 00:16:35.610
I don't know.

322
00:16:35.620 --> 00:16:38.200
Maybe the other John
Nolan will know.

323
00:16:38.210 --> 00:16:39.530
Oh. and we're
engaged. by the way.

324
00:16:39.540 --> 00:16:40.830
Oh. yeah. No. I know.

325
00:16:40.840 --> 00:16:42.200
It's just "girlfriend"
was funnier.

326
00:16:47.630 --> 00:16:48.930
Just take a seat.

327
00:16:50.300 --> 00:16:51.300
I'm good.

328
00:16:55.180 --> 00:16:56.550
He's gonna call.

329
00:16:56.560 --> 00:16:58.390
I'm glad you're so confident.

330
00:16:58.400 --> 00:17:00.220
But since I'm the one betting
my family's safety on the hope

331
00:17:00.230 --> 00:17:05.180
that he does. I'm
gonna keep pacing.

332
00:17:05.190 --> 00:17:07.640
Well. we knew that Elijah
was gonna be cautious.

333
00:17:07.650 --> 00:17:10.730
especially with the
information coming from you.

334
00:17:10.740 --> 00:17:13.190
And that's why we're gonna
give him a little push.

335
00:17:13.200 --> 00:17:15.990
As soon as he finds out that
Abril is after his guys.

336
00:17:16.000 --> 00:17:18.570
he's gonna be begging
for your help.

337
00:17:18.580 --> 00:17:20.370
And when exactly is this
psychological warfare

338
00:17:20.380 --> 00:17:21.790
supposed to begin?

339
00:17:23.630 --> 00:17:24.870
Right about now.

340
00:17:24.880 --> 00:17:27.460
Get off of me! This is B. S.!

341
00:17:27.470 --> 00:17:29.120
I didn't do anything wrong.

342
00:17:31.850 --> 00:17:33.000
I want my damn phone call.

343
00:17:34.510 --> 00:17:35.840
Remember us?

344
00:17:35.850 --> 00:17:37.130
How'd you find me?

345
00:17:37.140 --> 00:17:38.760
Foxburg is a small town.

346
00:17:38.770 --> 00:17:40.720
and you're not exactly
a criminal mastermind.

347
00:17:40.730 --> 00:17:42.470
Your eye looks pretty painful.

348
00:17:42.480 --> 00:17:44.680
Let me guess... Two
guys in a pickup truck

349
00:17:44.690 --> 00:17:45.930
find you before we did?

350
00:17:45.940 --> 00:17:50.480
What? No. I had a
little accident.

351
00:17:50.490 --> 00:17:52.690
Josh. here's the thing.
We're on a clock.

352
00:17:52.700 --> 00:17:54.070
We have a flight
to catch tomorrow.

353
00:17:54.080 --> 00:17:55.440
We don't have time
for your drama.

354
00:17:55.450 --> 00:17:57.570
So just tell us what those
guys were looking for

355
00:17:57.580 --> 00:17:58.990
in Evelyn's house.

356
00:17:59.000 --> 00:18:00.320
I don't know what
you're talking about.

357
00:18:00.330 --> 00:18:02.570
Come on. Knock it off.
You were clearly looking

358
00:18:02.580 --> 00:18:04.740
for something when we
met you at the house.

359
00:18:04.750 --> 00:18:07.410
Look. you don't owe my
mother anything. all right?

360
00:18:07.420 --> 00:18:10.290
That woman was a user
who felt no guilt

361
00:18:10.300 --> 00:18:13.040
about leaving other
people holding the bag.

362
00:18:13.050 --> 00:18:15.710
Just the sooner you cut
bait with her. the better.

363
00:18:15.720 --> 00:18:18.840
Do you think I don't know that?

364
00:18:18.850 --> 00:18:21.260
Look. I can't help
you. If you were smart.

365
00:18:21.270 --> 00:18:23.430
you'd move up your flight
and get the hell out of here.

366
00:18:27.190 --> 00:18:28.680
Lunch?

367
00:18:28.690 --> 00:18:29.490
Yeah.

368
00:18:29.490 --> 00:18:31.600
Nice work.

369
00:18:31.610 --> 00:18:32.730
How'd the other teams do?

370
00:18:32.740 --> 00:18:34.310
Good. good.

371
00:18:34.320 --> 00:18:36.020
All five of Elijah's
top lieutenants

372
00:18:36.030 --> 00:18:38.360
are in custody. quick
and quiet. as planned.

373
00:18:38.370 --> 00:18:41.360
Okay. So as long as no
one saw the arrests.

374
00:18:41.370 --> 00:18:43.990
Elijah just might believe
that Abril is responsible.

375
00:18:44.000 --> 00:18:45.620
But we can only hold
them for 12 hours

376
00:18:45.630 --> 00:18:47.660
before we have to let
them make a phone call.

377
00:18:47.670 --> 00:18:49.120
Think that's enough
time to spook Elijah?

378
00:18:49.130 --> 00:18:50.500
On its own. no.

379
00:18:50.510 --> 00:18:52.540
But we're not done
turning up the heat.

380
00:18:52.550 --> 00:18:55.500
Turns out our murdered
judge kept a diary.

381
00:18:55.510 --> 00:18:57.800
Laura and Brendon are on
their way to jack Monica up.

382
00:18:57.810 --> 00:19:00.920
And I got a plane to catch.

383
00:19:00.930 --> 00:19:04.340
Elijah. calm down. I haven't
heard anything about it.

384
00:19:04.350 --> 00:19:06.680
but I will check with my
sources inside the department

385
00:19:06.690 --> 00:19:08.430
and get back to you.

386
00:19:08.440 --> 00:19:10.480
Ms. Stevens. we have a
warrant for your arrest.

387
00:19:15.820 --> 00:19:17.860
Well. let me see it.

388
00:19:17.870 --> 00:19:19.900
I have a legal right to read it.

389
00:19:19.910 --> 00:19:21.700
Search warrants are being
conducted as we speak

390
00:19:21.710 --> 00:19:23.910
at your home and office.

391
00:19:23.920 --> 00:19:26.870
seizing all client files and
communications related to cases

392
00:19:26.880 --> 00:19:28.450
adjudicated by
Judge Daniel Rivas.

393
00:19:28.460 --> 00:19:29.540
It's... It's right there.

394
00:19:32.510 --> 00:19:35.080
Attorney-client privilege
expressly protects those files.

395
00:19:35.090 --> 00:19:39.250
Well. it did until you
bribed a federal judge

396
00:19:39.260 --> 00:19:41.630
looking for preferential
rulings for your clients.

397
00:19:43.230 --> 00:19:45.390
That's a lie. And this
warrant isn't worth

398
00:19:45.400 --> 00:19:47.260
the paper that it is printed on.

399
00:19:47.270 --> 00:19:49.510
When all this is
over and I walk away.

400
00:19:49.520 --> 00:19:52.640
I will take great pleasure
in shoving this up your...

401
00:19:52.650 --> 00:19:54.350
Okay. handcuff time.

402
00:19:54.360 --> 00:19:55.730
Turn around.

403
00:19:55.740 --> 00:19:56.900
I'll take your bag.

404
00:20:01.040 --> 00:20:02.570
Let's go.

405
00:20:54.880 --> 00:20:55.970
<i>Perfecto.</i>

406
00:21:17.150 --> 00:21:19.490
Go get them. guys.

407
00:21:22.240 --> 00:21:25.650
I'll say this about your
mom... That woman hustled.

408
00:21:25.670 --> 00:21:30.240
I mean. the sheer volume of
scams is a little awe-inspiring.

409
00:21:30.250 --> 00:21:33.490
I mean. luxury bottled air.

410
00:21:34.500 --> 00:21:35.660
Healing crystals.

411
00:21:35.670 --> 00:21:38.500
Oh.

412
00:21:38.510 --> 00:21:40.130
Enhancement undies.

413
00:21:40.140 --> 00:21:42.880
Don't forget the. uh.
Hair Today Shampoo.

414
00:21:42.890 --> 00:21:44.880
"Restores luster
to lifeless locks."

415
00:21:44.890 --> 00:21:46.010
Ooh. give me that.

416
00:21:46.040 --> 00:21:48.090
All my toiletries are
in the lost luggage.

417
00:21:48.100 --> 00:21:50.260
Yeah. I would not put this
anywhere near my hair.

418
00:21:50.270 --> 00:21:52.180
I think it's probably
gonna be motor oil

419
00:21:52.190 --> 00:21:54.390
or industrial
lubricant of some kind.

420
00:21:56.320 --> 00:21:57.480
- What? 
- Oh.

421
00:21:57.490 --> 00:21:59.940
Well. it's neither of those.

422
00:21:59.950 --> 00:22:01.270
What is it?

423
00:22:01.280 --> 00:22:03.320
It's not shampoo either.

424
00:22:03.330 --> 00:22:07.860
Don't say something bad.

425
00:22:07.870 --> 00:22:11.410
I'm thinking heroin.

426
00:22:11.420 --> 00:22:14.500
Mom.

427
00:22:16.210 --> 00:22:17.410
Johnny boy!

428
00:22:17.420 --> 00:22:19.330
Oh! McCheese!

429
00:22:19.340 --> 00:22:21.920
Get in here. Oh.
man. How are you?

430
00:22:21.930 --> 00:22:24.630
Oh. good to see you.

431
00:22:24.640 --> 00:22:27.590
Steve. this is Bailey
Nune. my fiancée.

432
00:22:27.600 --> 00:22:30.130
Wow. You went out to Hollywood
and hooked up with a starlet.

433
00:22:30.140 --> 00:22:32.470
It's nice to meet you.

434
00:22:32.480 --> 00:22:35.140
John told me you two were. um.
troublemakers back in the day.

435
00:22:35.150 --> 00:22:38.060
No comment. Although.
by the sounds of it.

436
00:22:38.070 --> 00:22:40.230
he's still getting into
trouble. Heroin shampoo?

437
00:22:40.240 --> 00:22:43.150
Yeah. This is not mine.
This is all Evelyn.

438
00:22:43.160 --> 00:22:45.320
Yeah. that sounds right.

439
00:22:45.330 --> 00:22:49.190
I mean. uh. I-I am
sorry for your loss.

440
00:22:49.200 --> 00:22:52.070
Uh. but the number of complaints
I got about your mom...

441
00:22:52.080 --> 00:22:53.870
Let's just say that there's
an entire file cabinet

442
00:22:53.880 --> 00:22:54.790
down at the station for her.

443
00:22:54.790 --> 00:22:56.370
So sorry about that.

444
00:22:56.380 --> 00:22:57.950
Did you get a chance to
run the plate we sent you?

445
00:22:57.960 --> 00:23:00.120
Oh. didn't have to.
Uh. Decker Conroy

446
00:23:00.130 --> 00:23:02.710
and his brother Perry...
They're at the center

447
00:23:02.720 --> 00:23:04.130
of the local drug
trade around here.

448
00:23:04.140 --> 00:23:06.090
I'll. uh... I'll go
to the usual haunts.

449
00:23:06.100 --> 00:23:07.340
Shouldn't take
long to find them.

450
00:23:07.350 --> 00:23:10.100
I may have an easier way.

451
00:23:17.360 --> 00:23:23.100
Hey. guys. Let me first just
say I'm sorry for how I reacted.

452
00:23:23.110 --> 00:23:24.330
I've been going through a lot.

453
00:23:24.360 --> 00:23:28.440
I. uh. got a lot going on here.
and I didn't have all the facts.

454
00:23:28.450 --> 00:23:30.880
Yeah. So what's up?

455
00:23:30.910 --> 00:23:32.650
That badge was fake or what?

456
00:23:32.660 --> 00:23:33.960
Oh. no. That's... That's real.

457
00:23:33.990 --> 00:23:36.870
I am a patrol officer with the
Los Angeles Police Department.

458
00:23:36.880 --> 00:23:38.580
which means. of
course. I don't have

459
00:23:38.590 --> 00:23:41.120
any legal jurisdiction
here in Pennsylvania.

460
00:23:41.130 --> 00:23:43.830
So. like. you
can't... can't even arrest us.

461
00:23:43.840 --> 00:23:46.080
That's right.

462
00:23:46.090 --> 00:23:49.220
So you can take your property.
and you're free to go.

463
00:23:53.360 --> 00:23:54.860
What about the guns. man?

464
00:23:54.890 --> 00:23:58.120
Oh. sorry. I gave those to a
cop who actually can arrest you.

465
00:23:58.730 --> 00:24:00.930
Howdy. boys. Drop the
bag. hands in the air.

466
00:24:00.940 --> 00:24:02.370
What the hell is this?

467
00:24:04.490 --> 00:24:05.770
Man.

468
00:24:07.490 --> 00:24:09.120
Here you go.

469
00:24:10.350 --> 00:24:11.780
But we should have
a proper catch up.

470
00:24:11.790 --> 00:24:13.150
I would love that.

471
00:24:13.170 --> 00:24:14.450
Though it's gonna have
to be in Los Angeles.

472
00:24:14.460 --> 00:24:15.630
We are out of here tomorrow.

473
00:24:16.400 --> 00:24:18.450
Have a nice flight.

474
00:24:18.460 --> 00:24:20.200
- Anyway. Cheese.
- Take care. Johnny boy.

475
00:24:22.710 --> 00:24:24.580
So. where were we?

476
00:24:24.590 --> 00:24:25.590
Barely started.

477
00:24:25.590 --> 00:24:27.080
Right.

478
00:24:32.020 --> 00:24:33.420
Love the outfit.

479
00:24:33.430 --> 00:24:35.930
Oh. I'm sorry. Did
you say something?

480
00:24:35.940 --> 00:24:38.430
I was busy writing a
lawsuit in my head.

481
00:24:38.440 --> 00:24:42.270
I'm Supervisory Special Agent
Matthew Garza with the FBI.

482
00:24:42.280 --> 00:24:44.180
You've been apprised of
the charges against you.

483
00:24:44.190 --> 00:24:46.140
and I'd like to give you an
opportunity to address them.

484
00:24:46.150 --> 00:24:48.520
Thank you. but I'll
wait for my lawyer.

485
00:24:48.530 --> 00:24:49.730
As is your right.

486
00:24:49.740 --> 00:24:51.520
Mm.

487
00:24:51.530 --> 00:24:54.400
But you did bribe
a federal judge.

488
00:24:54.410 --> 00:24:56.200
and we believe that you're
responsible for his death.

489
00:24:56.210 --> 00:24:58.410
But see. that's not
your real problem.

490
00:24:58.420 --> 00:25:01.460
Your real problem is that
you failed your boss.

491
00:25:03.300 --> 00:25:05.080
You exposed Elijah's
organization

492
00:25:05.090 --> 00:25:07.710
to an FBI investigation.
And one day soon.

493
00:25:07.720 --> 00:25:10.460
whether you are under
house arrest or in jail.

494
00:25:10.470 --> 00:25:13.170
he's gonna have you killed.

495
00:25:13.180 --> 00:25:16.840
Oh.
no. I'm so scared.

496
00:25:16.850 --> 00:25:19.050
Listen. if you think
I'm gonna betray my oath

497
00:25:19.060 --> 00:25:20.510
as a lawyer the way Wesley did.

498
00:25:20.520 --> 00:25:22.140
you're a moron.

499
00:25:22.150 --> 00:25:24.520
And don't bother offering
me witness protection.

500
00:25:24.530 --> 00:25:27.100
You think I'm gonna work at
a Cinnabon in Albuquerque?

501
00:25:27.110 --> 00:25:28.600
I'd rather be shanked in prison.

502
00:25:28.610 --> 00:25:31.230
No. you wouldn't.
You're a survivor.

503
00:25:31.240 --> 00:25:33.400
Exactly.

504
00:25:33.410 --> 00:25:36.750
So kindly get out of my face
until my lawyer arrives.

505
00:25:38.250 --> 00:25:39.580
Arrested for what?

506
00:25:42.460 --> 00:25:45.750
<i>Where did you hear that.
and where is she being held?</i>

507
00:25:45.760 --> 00:25:48.920
Sounds like he
heard about Monica.

508
00:25:48.930 --> 00:25:50.830
<i>Well. find out.</i>

509
00:25:50.840 --> 00:25:52.790
<i>What about Hazy and the others?</i>

510
00:25:52.800 --> 00:25:54.170
And he's missing
his lieutenants.

511
00:25:55.770 --> 00:25:57.300
<i>Listen to me.</i>

512
00:25:57.310 --> 00:25:59.050
I'm calling you
back in 10 minutes.

513
00:25:59.060 --> 00:26:00.840
And if you don't have an answer.

514
00:26:00.850 --> 00:26:03.100
you're going missing. too.

515
00:26:03.110 --> 00:26:05.520
Not over the phone. boss.

516
00:26:05.530 --> 00:26:08.100
What are you doing?

517
00:26:08.110 --> 00:26:09.950
Getting some clarity.

518
00:26:27.960 --> 00:26:29.960
<i>Took you
long enough to call.</i>

519
00:26:36.310 --> 00:26:37.710
Satisfied?

520
00:26:37.720 --> 00:26:39.670
Never.

521
00:26:47.780 --> 00:26:50.180
I'm accepting your offer.

522
00:26:50.190 --> 00:26:52.190
Tell me how to take
down Abril's hitters.

523
00:26:52.200 --> 00:26:53.730
and you and your
family are safe.

524
00:26:53.740 --> 00:26:55.360
You don't have much time.

525
00:26:55.370 --> 00:26:57.690
They've already taken out
your street-level bosses.

526
00:26:57.700 --> 00:26:59.740
Word is they came heavy.

527
00:26:59.750 --> 00:27:02.280
Well. heavy won't
matter in an ambush.

528
00:27:02.290 --> 00:27:05.580
And I got firepower for days.

529
00:27:05.590 --> 00:27:07.660
They're staying at a
house in North Hollywood.

530
00:27:07.670 --> 00:27:09.950
She brought two specialists
with her from Guatemala.

531
00:27:09.960 --> 00:27:11.580
The rest is local muscle.

532
00:27:11.590 --> 00:27:13.120
Is the task force up on her yet?

533
00:27:13.130 --> 00:27:14.540
No. She won't be
here long enough.

534
00:27:14.550 --> 00:27:16.470
and we won't have
time to get warrants.

535
00:27:16.500 --> 00:27:18.780
She's here to hit
you and you fly home.

536
00:27:18.930 --> 00:27:21.260
so you need to move first.

537
00:27:22.810 --> 00:27:26.600
Well. I guess this is goodbye...

538
00:27:26.610 --> 00:27:29.720
unless something goes wrong.

539
00:27:29.730 --> 00:27:31.430
Make sure it doesn't.

540
00:27:31.440 --> 00:27:33.020
I did my part.

541
00:27:42.710 --> 00:27:46.490
Get a team together.
Recon the location.

542
00:27:46.500 --> 00:27:50.580
If everything is on the
up. we hit them tonight.

543
00:28:09.230 --> 00:28:10.940
He took the bait. It's
going down tonight.

544
00:28:16.070 --> 00:28:17.910
Can't <i>wait</i> to see who that is.

545
00:28:25.330 --> 00:28:26.990
Stacy!

546
00:28:27.000 --> 00:28:29.490
I figured you'd be swamped. so
I swung by the Sunrise Diner.

547
00:28:29.500 --> 00:28:32.250
You did not get me a
pulled pork sandwich.

548
00:28:32.260 --> 00:28:33.910
I did not.

549
00:28:33.920 --> 00:28:35.920
I brought you two.

550
00:28:35.930 --> 00:28:37.630
You are an angel
straight from heaven.

551
00:28:37.640 --> 00:28:38.920
Two of what?

552
00:28:38.930 --> 00:28:40.340
Two of the best sandwiches

553
00:28:40.350 --> 00:28:42.710
you have ever tasted
in your entire life.

554
00:28:42.720 --> 00:28:44.720
And I have two for you. as well.

555
00:28:47.100 --> 00:28:48.930
I apologize. by the
way. for the mess.

556
00:28:48.940 --> 00:28:51.930
No. not at all. I can't imagine
how hard this must be for you.

557
00:28:51.940 --> 00:28:54.730
Do you want wine? I think
I saw a box in the fridge.

558
00:28:54.740 --> 00:28:56.270
Way ahead of you. Oh.

559
00:28:56.280 --> 00:28:58.730
And a beer for John.

560
00:28:58.740 --> 00:28:59.900
Marry me.

561
00:28:59.910 --> 00:29:01.860
Sadly. you're already engaged.

562
00:29:01.870 --> 00:29:04.240
Who am I to stand in
the way of true love?

563
00:29:04.250 --> 00:29:06.400
John did tell me earlier you
were the one that got away.

564
00:29:06.410 --> 00:29:09.120
Aww! That just made my day.

565
00:29:09.130 --> 00:29:11.200
But he's all yours.

566
00:29:11.210 --> 00:29:12.950
I got the new boyfriend
perfectly trained.

567
00:29:12.960 --> 00:29:14.540
and I don't have the
strength to start again.

568
00:29:14.550 --> 00:29:15.550
He is a lot of work.

569
00:29:15.550 --> 00:29:16.470
I'm right here.

570
00:29:19.550 --> 00:29:21.500
What was that?

571
00:29:21.510 --> 00:29:22.800
Stay behind me.

572
00:29:22.810 --> 00:29:24.710
Is that necessary?

573
00:29:24.720 --> 00:29:26.340
We've already had quite the day.

574
00:29:34.440 --> 00:29:35.980
Josh!

575
00:29:35.990 --> 00:29:36.900
What the hell are you doing?

576
00:29:36.900 --> 00:29:39.230
Nothing.

577
00:29:39.240 --> 00:29:40.650
Josh?

578
00:29:41.380 --> 00:29:43.510
I'm looking for the spare
set of keys to Evelyn's car.

579
00:29:43.620 --> 00:29:45.820
You broke in to steal
his mother's car?

580
00:29:45.830 --> 00:29:47.570
Josh. you know better than that.

581
00:29:47.580 --> 00:29:49.360
I wish that were true.

582
00:29:49.370 --> 00:29:51.660
Josh. why are you
stealing my mom's car?

583
00:29:51.670 --> 00:29:52.700
'Cause. I'm a dead
man if I don't get

584
00:29:52.710 --> 00:29:53.810
the hell out of Foxburg.

585
00:29:53.840 --> 00:29:56.330
Hey. hey. hey. Does
this have anything to do

586
00:29:56.340 --> 00:29:58.290
with the drugs you've been
selling with my mother.

587
00:29:58.300 --> 00:30:01.170
W... The fake supplements
were her idea.

588
00:30:01.180 --> 00:30:03.420
No. not the
supplements. the heroin.

589
00:30:03.430 --> 00:30:05.630
She was selling heroin?!

590
00:30:05.640 --> 00:30:07.720
And didn't cut me in?

591
00:30:07.730 --> 00:30:08.870
Eh. it doesn't matter.

592
00:30:08.890 --> 00:30:10.100
She would have just screwed
me over like she did

593
00:30:10.100 --> 00:30:11.590
with the generators.

594
00:30:11.600 --> 00:30:12.490
I'm afraid to ask.

595
00:30:12.520 --> 00:30:13.520
Me too.

596
00:30:13.540 --> 00:30:14.980
I'm game.

597
00:30:15.860 --> 00:30:17.790
What generators?

598
00:30:18.240 --> 00:30:20.850
Evelyn and I sold a bunch
of portable generators

599
00:30:20.860 --> 00:30:23.110
to a group of people.
and they're unhappy.

600
00:30:23.120 --> 00:30:25.570
Okay. What group of people?

601
00:30:25.580 --> 00:30:28.570
They. you know. like guns and
don't like the government.

602
00:30:28.580 --> 00:30:30.150
Like a militia?

603
00:30:30.160 --> 00:30:31.360
Yes. a militia!

604
00:30:31.370 --> 00:30:33.160
Why do they want you dead?

605
00:30:33.170 --> 00:30:34.950
Apparently. the reason your
mother got such a good deal

606
00:30:34.960 --> 00:30:36.740
is because they're defective.

607
00:30:36.750 --> 00:30:39.710
As was my mother. Just
give them the money back.

608
00:30:39.720 --> 00:30:41.580
I can't! It's gone!

609
00:30:41.590 --> 00:30:44.960
She must have used it
all on her next big idea.

610
00:30:44.970 --> 00:30:46.500
Okay. Well. you're
not getting the car

611
00:30:46.510 --> 00:30:47.760
'cause I already sold it online.

612
00:30:47.770 --> 00:30:49.630
Look. your best bet here

613
00:30:49.640 --> 00:30:52.220
is just go pay Steve a visit
at the sheriff's station

614
00:30:52.230 --> 00:30:53.800
and just throw
yourself on his mercy.

615
00:30:53.810 --> 00:30:55.350
Yeah. I'm not gonna do that.

616
00:30:55.360 --> 00:30:56.760
No. h-he's just gonna
rub it in my face.

617
00:30:56.770 --> 00:30:58.430
and I'm not giving
him the satisfaction.

618
00:30:58.440 --> 00:31:02.770
Josh. that is a dumb reason
to avoid asking for help.

619
00:31:05.320 --> 00:31:07.570
Okay. Okay.

620
00:31:10.200 --> 00:31:12.070
Here.

621
00:31:12.080 --> 00:31:13.820
Josh.

622
00:31:17.500 --> 00:31:20.200
Bullet went all the way
through. He's lucky.

623
00:31:20.210 --> 00:31:21.910
That's the militia outside!

624
00:31:21.920 --> 00:31:23.370
Yeah. I figured that out.

625
00:31:23.380 --> 00:31:25.210
I need to stop the bleeding.

626
00:31:27.220 --> 00:31:28.550
Will this work?

627
00:31:28.560 --> 00:31:30.510
Yeah. actually.

628
00:31:30.520 --> 00:31:32.260
What the hell are you doing?!

629
00:31:32.270 --> 00:31:33.680
Saving your life.

630
00:31:37.570 --> 00:31:39.220
Stacy. you okay?

631
00:31:39.230 --> 00:31:40.680
I'm starting to think
you're bad luck.

632
00:31:40.690 --> 00:31:42.020
Yeah. I get that a lot.

633
00:31:42.030 --> 00:31:43.810
Call Steve. tell
him to bring backup.

634
00:31:43.820 --> 00:31:44.820
Do you have any more magazines?

635
00:31:44.820 --> 00:31:45.820
Nine rounds left.

636
00:31:48.830 --> 00:31:52.030
Steve's on his way
with the state police.

637
00:31:52.040 --> 00:31:53.500
Taser.

638
00:31:59.710 --> 00:32:01.420
- Reload. 
- Okay.

639
00:32:13.390 --> 00:32:16.760
Okay. All right. Uh...

640
00:32:19.440 --> 00:32:20.820
Ladies.

641
00:32:24.070 --> 00:32:25.100
John. what do you got?

642
00:32:26.110 --> 00:32:27.480
It's okay. We're Code-4.

643
00:32:27.490 --> 00:32:28.900
Anybody hurt?

644
00:32:28.910 --> 00:32:30.520
Yeah. Josh is gonna
need an ambulance...

645
00:32:30.530 --> 00:32:32.190
GSW to the abdomen.

646
00:32:32.200 --> 00:32:33.950
Three more GSWs to the
guys who attacked us.

647
00:32:33.960 --> 00:32:35.570
Nothing personal. Johnny boy.

648
00:32:35.580 --> 00:32:37.200
but I cannot wait for
you to go back to L. A.

649
00:32:37.210 --> 00:32:38.570
You and me both.

650
00:32:38.580 --> 00:32:41.340
And me.

651
00:33:10.910 --> 00:33:13.110
Feels like they're buying it.

652
00:33:13.120 --> 00:33:16.030
Well. they haven't left
yet. That's a good sign.

653
00:33:16.040 --> 00:33:18.410
<i>They buying it?</i>

654
00:33:18.420 --> 00:33:22.830
<i>So far.</i>

655
00:33:22.840 --> 00:33:25.250
Guys. I'm feeling a little
vulnerable right now.

656
00:33:25.260 --> 00:33:26.580
What if they decide
to start shooting?

657
00:33:26.590 --> 00:33:28.460
You're doing great.

658
00:33:28.470 --> 00:33:31.920
Lucky for us. you're a
match for our psycho killer.

659
00:33:31.930 --> 00:33:34.170
Now move away from the window.

660
00:33:34.180 --> 00:33:35.550
We got to tease
them a little bit.

661
00:33:35.560 --> 00:33:36.970
give them that itch.

662
00:33:41.400 --> 00:33:43.640
Why haven't they called
Elijah to get the green light?

663
00:33:43.650 --> 00:33:45.560
'Cause they're good
at their jobs...

664
00:33:45.570 --> 00:33:48.020
Measure twice. cut once.

665
00:33:48.030 --> 00:33:50.190
Lopez. you think Elijah
just sends them in

666
00:33:50.200 --> 00:33:52.440
once he decides it's safe?

667
00:33:52.450 --> 00:33:54.110
No. He'll want to be here.

668
00:33:54.120 --> 00:33:55.940
Elijah's ego's too big
to let someone else hit

669
00:33:55.950 --> 00:33:58.070
Abril's people for him.

670
00:33:58.080 --> 00:33:59.990
<i>Alpha Team. status check.</i>

671
00:34:00.000 --> 00:34:02.120
They're circling...
Making their way closer.

672
00:34:02.130 --> 00:34:03.530
He's clearly
checking for a tail.

673
00:34:03.540 --> 00:34:05.240
but we're doing
multiple handoffs.

674
00:34:05.250 --> 00:34:07.250
It's nice to have
federal resources.

675
00:34:09.130 --> 00:34:10.620
C'mon. make the call.

676
00:34:14.470 --> 00:34:15.630
Still no sign of a tail?

677
00:34:18.480 --> 00:34:20.220
Mnh-mnh. No.

678
00:34:20.230 --> 00:34:21.590
All right.

679
00:34:28.360 --> 00:34:32.730
Yo. three inside.
Partying a little.

680
00:34:32.740 --> 00:34:36.230
Clocked a few
noisemakers... Loud ones.

681
00:34:36.240 --> 00:34:37.820
Here we go.

682
00:34:37.830 --> 00:34:39.530
<i>Any sign of eyeballs?</i>

683
00:34:39.540 --> 00:34:42.660
None. LJ took a lap around
the block... all quiet.

684
00:34:44.290 --> 00:34:46.660
<i>But we should wait till later.</i>

685
00:34:46.670 --> 00:34:50.210
Maybe. But what if some
of their friends show up?

686
00:34:50.220 --> 00:34:52.670
Suddenly we're going
to a much bigger party.

687
00:34:52.680 --> 00:34:57.090
Turn right here.
look for follow cars.

688
00:34:57.100 --> 00:34:58.510
Keep going straight.

689
00:35:02.100 --> 00:35:05.640
Alpha Team handing off.

690
00:35:05.650 --> 00:35:07.430
<i>Copy.
Bravo has contact.</i>

691
00:35:10.530 --> 00:35:13.310
Alpha Team headed to safe
house. ETA two minutes.

692
00:35:16.580 --> 00:35:17.820
You still there?

693
00:35:17.830 --> 00:35:20.400
Yeah. I think we're clear.

694
00:35:20.410 --> 00:35:21.900
And I think we can't wait.

695
00:35:21.910 --> 00:35:23.240
The goal is the out of towners.

696
00:35:23.250 --> 00:35:24.820
We can visit the
locals any time.

697
00:35:24.830 --> 00:35:26.280
<i>I need a yes or a no.</i>

698
00:35:38.220 --> 00:35:40.380
I don't know. boss.

699
00:35:40.390 --> 00:35:41.670
I think we should wait.

700
00:35:41.680 --> 00:35:44.340
Yes or no?

701
00:35:45.560 --> 00:35:47.220
Say yes.

702
00:35:52.820 --> 00:35:54.810
Yes.

703
00:35:54.820 --> 00:35:56.900
I'll be there in a minute.

704
00:35:56.910 --> 00:35:58.570
All right. here we go.

705
00:35:58.580 --> 00:36:00.730
Remember. we need the target to
be armed and on the premises.

706
00:36:00.740 --> 00:36:02.650
<i>Once they make armed
unlawful entry.</i>

707
00:36:02.660 --> 00:36:04.200
<i>then we can take them
down. Not before. Alright.</i>

708
00:36:22.480 --> 00:36:24.050
Target on site.

709
00:36:43.320 --> 00:36:44.860
Copy. House Team in position.

710
00:37:02.470 --> 00:37:04.380
Here we go. They're
on the move.

711
00:37:42.350 --> 00:37:43.850
No.

712
00:37:45.390 --> 00:37:46.670
No.

713
00:37:51.310 --> 00:37:53.680
It's over. All
teams stand down.

714
00:37:55.280 --> 00:37:56.980
<i>It's over.</i>

715
00:38:04.080 --> 00:38:05.780
Screw that. We can arrest
them. They're right there.

716
00:38:07.500 --> 00:38:09.570
For gun charges? That will
only hold them for a minute.

717
00:38:09.580 --> 00:38:10.610
That's not enough.

718
00:38:19.680 --> 00:38:21.580
He walked away. so we do. too.

719
00:38:21.590 --> 00:38:23.340
And then what?

720
00:38:23.350 --> 00:38:25.210
We go back to work.
find another way.

721
00:38:28.770 --> 00:38:30.380
Let her go.

722
00:38:35.930 --> 00:38:38.100
Well. where do
you want to start?

723
00:38:38.120 --> 00:38:40.290
You mentioned something
about a controlled burn?

724
00:38:40.320 --> 00:38:42.770
You know. there's this
little thing I like to call

725
00:38:42.780 --> 00:38:45.360
throwing money at the problem.

726
00:38:45.370 --> 00:38:46.530
Hire someone? Yes.

727
00:38:46.540 --> 00:38:47.650
Oh. my God. I love it.

728
00:38:47.660 --> 00:38:48.940
Why the hell didn't
I think of that?

729
00:38:48.960 --> 00:38:51.610
Great. Let's just get the photo
albums and be done with it.

730
00:38:51.620 --> 00:38:53.420
I saw them over here.

731
00:38:55.710 --> 00:38:58.830
Oh. I forgot all
about this.

732
00:38:58.840 --> 00:39:00.370
Oh. who signed it?

733
00:39:00.380 --> 00:39:03.330
Mike Schmidt. best
player in Philly history.

734
00:39:03.340 --> 00:39:05.170
It's our baseball team.

735
00:39:05.180 --> 00:39:07.300
I love when you mansplain...
Although I'd argue

736
00:39:07.310 --> 00:39:09.670
that Steve Carlton gave
Schmidt a run for his money.

737
00:39:09.680 --> 00:39:10.920
Unless you're one of those

738
00:39:10.930 --> 00:39:13.780
"pitchers can't
be MVPs" cavemen.

739
00:39:13.810 --> 00:39:15.980
Guilty as charged.
No. I remember my mom

740
00:39:16.000 --> 00:39:19.210
got us tickets to this game
and then talked our way

741
00:39:19.240 --> 00:39:21.030
past the security guard
to get him to sign it.

742
00:39:21.050 --> 00:39:23.010
Man. I can't believe
she didn't sell it.

743
00:39:23.030 --> 00:39:24.990
I think we should put
that on our mantle.

744
00:39:25.030 --> 00:39:26.650
That's a great idea.

745
00:39:26.660 --> 00:39:27.740
Look on the bright side...

746
00:39:27.770 --> 00:39:30.150
The last 24 hours have been
a little slice of hell.

747
00:39:30.160 --> 00:39:32.110
but this house is
more inheritance

748
00:39:32.120 --> 00:39:33.640
than most people get.

749
00:39:33.660 --> 00:39:36.080
You could sell it. pay for
the "Parental Trauma" package

750
00:39:36.090 --> 00:39:37.580
and the cleanup crew.

751
00:39:37.590 --> 00:39:39.660
and still turn a
pretty healthy profit.

752
00:39:39.670 --> 00:39:41.660
I think that sounds
like a great plan.

753
00:39:41.670 --> 00:39:43.750
Yeah. Knock knock.

754
00:39:43.760 --> 00:39:46.340
Hey. How are you feeling?

755
00:39:46.350 --> 00:39:47.630
- About last night? 
- Yeah.

756
00:39:47.640 --> 00:39:50.300
I'm fine.

757
00:39:50.310 --> 00:39:51.670
But there's something
I need to tell you.

758
00:39:51.680 --> 00:39:53.840
Uh-oh. Yeah. I was looking

759
00:39:53.850 --> 00:39:56.500
at your mom's
accounts. and. well.

760
00:39:56.520 --> 00:39:58.510
the bank's foreclosing
on the house.

761
00:39:58.520 --> 00:40:01.930
She hadn't paid the mortgage
in a year. It's a done deal.

762
00:40:01.940 --> 00:40:04.560
I'm sorry.

763
00:40:07.660 --> 00:40:12.900
That... That is the perfect
ending to this whole debacle.

764
00:40:12.910 --> 00:40:15.820
Here you go. It's all yours.
We have a plane to catch.

765
00:40:15.830 --> 00:40:17.490
I... What. what?

766
00:40:17.500 --> 00:40:19.450
It was so nice to meet
you. Please come visit.

767
00:40:19.460 --> 00:40:21.750
We have lots of room. Okay?

768
00:40:21.760 --> 00:40:24.330
Got a delivery for Evelyn Nolan.

769
00:40:24.340 --> 00:40:26.630
Let me guess. you got
about $100.000 worth

770
00:40:26.640 --> 00:40:27.880
of something ridiculous?

771
00:40:27.890 --> 00:40:29.040
My money's on diet supplement.

772
00:40:29.050 --> 00:40:30.670
I'm feeling... food
storage systems.

773
00:40:30.680 --> 00:40:33.090
Ah. Protein shakes.

774
00:40:33.100 --> 00:40:34.840
Can one of you sign
for the delivery?

775
00:40:34.850 --> 00:40:37.850
No. no. Sorry. We don't
know. uh. Evelyn Nolan.

776
00:40:37.860 --> 00:40:39.050
No. you can talk to her. though.

777
00:40:39.060 --> 00:40:41.180
Thank you. Stacy.
for everything. Bye.

778
00:40:41.200 --> 00:40:42.200
Run.

779
00:40:43.650 --> 00:40:46.060
Jack's down for his nap.

780
00:40:46.070 --> 00:40:48.150
I don't know if I'll
ever sleep again.

781
00:40:48.160 --> 00:40:49.690
Try not to worry.

782
00:40:49.700 --> 00:40:52.740
We've got units parked in
the front and back 24/7.

783
00:40:52.750 --> 00:40:56.070
and Garza sent a very
clear message to Elijah

784
00:40:56.080 --> 00:40:58.840
that we're off-limits.

785
00:40:58.870 --> 00:41:00.070
You really think he'll listen?

786
00:41:00.960 --> 00:41:02.750
For the near future.

787
00:41:02.760 --> 00:41:06.080
while he figures out how
much exposure he's facing.

788
00:41:06.090 --> 00:41:08.000
Did you really threaten
to fight Elijah

789
00:41:08.010 --> 00:41:10.170
in the street with
a claw hammer?

790
00:41:10.180 --> 00:41:11.980
Grey heard it on the wire.

791
00:41:12.010 --> 00:41:14.920
I did. But it was all a bluff.

792
00:41:14.930 --> 00:41:17.840
I'd dust him from a thousand
yards with a 220 grain.

793
00:41:17.850 --> 00:41:20.350
disappear before the sound
wave even reached him.

794
00:41:20.360 --> 00:41:21.650
You're kidding. right?

795
00:41:23.070 --> 00:41:24.390
Yeah.

796
00:41:24.400 --> 00:41:26.350
Mm.

797
00:41:26.360 --> 00:41:28.060
I think if all else fails.
we should just break open

798
00:41:28.070 --> 00:41:30.940
the trust fund.
just buy an island.

799
00:41:30.950 --> 00:41:32.450
I'm not running.

800
00:41:34.410 --> 00:41:36.200
I know.

801
00:41:36.210 --> 00:41:38.070
But maybe we could
buy an island anyway.

802
00:41:38.080 --> 00:41:41.530
I'll send
you some listings.

803
00:41:41.540 --> 00:41:43.130
What about Abril?

804
00:41:45.920 --> 00:41:49.080
I think we're in
the clear for now.

805
00:41:49.090 --> 00:41:51.420
As far as she knows.
Daylin and the Sicarios

806
00:41:51.430 --> 00:41:52.840
were sent right back home

807
00:41:52.850 --> 00:41:54.590
because they're on a
federal watch list.

808
00:41:54.600 --> 00:41:56.420
Mm. I can't imagine
she has any idea

809
00:41:56.430 --> 00:41:58.930
about the con we
just ran on Elijah.

810
00:42:04.400 --> 00:42:07.310
And now it all makes sense.

811
00:42:07.320 --> 00:42:10.520
Well. this isn't
a zero sum game.

812
00:42:10.530 --> 00:42:14.190
We can help each other.

813
00:42:18.000 --> 00:42:19.080
I'm listening.
